        <updateDate>2016-11-07T22:07:30Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Great Lakes Pipeline Safety Act of 2016</b></p> <p>This bill directs the Department of Transportation (DOT) to conduct a study to determine the economic and environmental risks of oil or hazardous liquids spills or leaks in the Straits of Mackinac that a failure of onshore, underwater pipeline facilities within the straits would pose to the Great Lakes.</p> <p>In addition, DOT must evaluate the condition and structural integrity of the facilities.</p> <p>DOT shall terminate operations of a facility upon a determination, based on such studies, that risk of hazard to life, property, or the environment warrants termination. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
